scheduled_activities.activity: Fall 2023 - Muay Thai Club - Beginner - Tuesdays 1:00-2:30pm
scheduled_activities.description:
Muay Thai is a striking martial art that weaponizes fists, elbows, knees and legs. This art of 8 limbs increases speed, endurance, strength, coordination and flexibility. Aimed at beginner to intermediates, classes include a fun, challenging workout and the basics of standup fighting. Expect skipping, calisthenics, shadowboxing and partner work - so bring a friend!

The club strives to build mentally and physically high performing student athletes with a strong sense of philanthropy

Fall 2023 - Swimming - Trans & Non-binary, 2SLGBTQ+ open rec - Trans & Non-binary
scheduled_activities.description:
Take a break and enjoy the PAC pool under the supervision Lifeguards. Swim, play basketball or bounce off the diving board! Lanes are available for lengths and recreational swimming and the diving well is open during this time. The PAC “Admissions Policy” and Swim Tests apply to all swims. ** Please note there may be cancellations due to facility closures or other department bookings.

Trans and Non-binary programming aims to provide a safer, comfortable, inclusive, and fun atmosphere
